/code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die Funktion <code><strong>Math.acos()</strong></code> gibt den Arkuskosinus (im Radiantenmaß) einer Zahl zurück:</p>\n\n<p><math display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∀</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>∊</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo>,</mo><mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace><mstyle mathvariant=\"monospace\"><mrow><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"thinmathspace\">Math.acos</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mstyle><mo>=</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">arccos</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mtext> das gleiche </mtext><mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace><mi>y</mi><mo>∊</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>;</mo><mi>π</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace><mtext>derart, dass</mtext><mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">cos</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"TeX\">\\forall x \\in [{-1};1],\\;\\mathtt{\\operatorname{Math.acos}(x)} = \\arccos(x) = \\text{ das gleiche } \\; y \\in [0; \\pi] \\, \\text{derart, dass} \\; \\cos(y)</annotation></semantics></math></p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/math-acos.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\">Math.acos(<em>x</em>) </pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameter","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"x\"><code>x</code></dt>\n <dd>Eine Zahl.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"rückgabewert","title":"Rückgabewert","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Der Arkuskosinus (im Radiantenmaß) der übergebenen Zahl, wenn diese zwischen <strong>-1</strong> und <strong>1</strong> ist. Anderfalls wird <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurückgegeben.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Die <code>acos</code> Methode gibt einen numerischen Wert zwischen 0 und <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/PI\"><code>Pi</code></a> im Radiantenmaß für x Werte zwischen -1 und 1 zurück.&nbsp; Wenn der übergebene Wert außerhalb dieses Bereiches liegt, wird <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurückgegeben.</p>\n\n<p>Weil <code>acos</code> eine statische Methode von <code>Math</code> ist, kann dieses immer mit <code>Math.acos()</code> genutzt werden, ohne dass ein Objekt von <code>Math</code> erstellt werden muss (<code>Math</code> ist kein Konstruktor).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_math.acos","title":"Beispiel: <code>Math.acos</code> benutzen","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush:js notranslate\"><code>Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">acos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">acos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// 3.141592653589793</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">acos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// 1.5707963267948966</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">acos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0.5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 1.0471975511965979</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">acos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// 0</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">acos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Für Werte kleiner -1 oder größer 1 gibt <code>Math.acos</code> <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurück.</p>","titleAsText":"Beispiel: Math.acos benutzen"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST-ARCH/ECMA-262,%201st%20edition,%20June%201997.pdf\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.0.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.8.2.2\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.acos' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-math.acos\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.acos' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-math.acos\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.acos' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Math.acos","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/acos/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/asin\"><code>Math.asin()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/atan\"><code>Math.atan()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/atan2\"><code>Math.atan2()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/cos\"><code>Math.cos()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/sin\"><code>Math.sin()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/tan\"><code>Math.tan()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"description"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"examples"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Die Funktion Math.acos() gibt den Arkuskosinus (im Radiantenmaß) einer Zahl zurück:","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Math.acos()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Math.acos()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Math.acos()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Math.a